	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_000468_0001"><!--pb/@n='1r'--></pb>
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName><settlement type="city">Glasgow</settlement></placeName><date when="1840-11-16">16<hi rend="sup">th</hi> November 
<lb/>1840</date></p>
<lb/><p rend="left">My Dear Sir</p>
<lb/><p>I refrained writing you 
<lb/>respecting the books to be presented to <persName>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Bennett</persName>
<lb/><choice><orig>untill</orig><reg>until</reg></choice> I could inform you of the result of 
<lb/>the examination I underwent this morning</p>
<lb/><p>After about an hour's examination 
<lb/>I was elected member of the "Faculty of 
<lb/>Physicians &amp;Surgeons, <placeName><settlement type="city">Glasgow</settlement></placeName>" so the 
<lb/>chief object of my journey to <placeName><country>Scotland</country></placeName>
<lb/>has been successfully accomplished</p>
<lb/><p>I intend going to <placeName><settlement type="town">Hamilton</settlement></placeName> this 
<lb/>evening to pay a short visit to 
<lb/>my parents &amp; afterwards will leave 
<lb/><placeName><settlement type="city">Glasgow</settlement></placeName> so as to be in <placeName><settlement type="city">London</settlement></placeName> on 
<lb/>Thursday night or early on Friday morning</p>
<lb/><p><persName>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Bennett</persName> said he should like 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_000468_0002"><!--pb/@n='1v'--></pb>
<lb/>to have either "<persName>Ellis</persName>' <placeName><country>Madagascar</country></placeName>" or the 
<lb/>new work which comes out <del type="cancelled">next</del><add place="above">this</add> week 
<lb/>Most of the others he has read-_</p>
<lb/><p>Perhaps both of the above mentioned 
<lb/>works might be given him, as he 
<lb/>well deserves them.</p>
<lb/><p><persName><choice><abbr>M<hi rend="sup">rs.</hi></abbr><expan>Misters</expan></choice> Taylor</persName> &amp; <persName>Inglis</persName> are both well 
<lb/>&amp; pursuing their studies vigourously. They 
<lb/>desire me to present you their very 
<lb/>kind regards</p>
<lb/><p rend="center">Yours Affectionately</p>
<lb/><p rend="right"><persName><hi rend="underline">David <choice><orig>Livingston</orig><reg>Livingstone</reg></choice></hi></persName></p>
<lb/><p><persName><hi rend="underline">Rev.<hi rend="sup">d</hi> J. Arundel</hi></persName></p>

